TY  - JOUR
T1  - Simulation of a Simplified Job Shop
AU  - Baker, C. T.
AU  - Dzielinski, B. P.
Y1  - 1960/04/01
PY  - 1960
DA  - 1960/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.6.3.311
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.6.3.311
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 311
EP  - 323
VL  - 6
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This is a report of the results of some digital computer simulation studies of a simplified model of a job shop production process. Such factors as the average effectiveness of schedules under the impact of random variations in processing times and the effect of changing operating policies are considered. The average manufacturing times and predictability of completion times were used as measures of effectiveness.
AB  - This is a report of the results of some digital computer simulation studies of a simplified model of a job shop production process. Such factors as the average effectiveness of schedules under the impact of random variations in processing times and the effect of changing operating policies are considered. The average manufacturing times and predictability of completion times were used as measures of effectiveness.
